{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782666351843,"sessionID":"ses_0f0cebc45ffeXm04RK0z9p3ABS","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_TfaYJJsM5B2egPyqEcgZz30J","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\translation-inputs\\coverage-gap-report.md","limit":300,"offset":1},"output":"<path>D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\translation-inputs\\coverage-gap-report.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Coverage Gap Report\n2: \n3: ## Goal\n4: \n5: Reduce functional coverage gaps first, and use code-scale gaps as a warning signal for unexplained omission. Matching source LoC exactly is not required; every large reduction should be explained by concrete framework replacement, generated resource mapping, or an explicit deferred item. A healthy target/source LoC ratio is not proof of feature coverage; verify the coverage matrix, platform capability check, resources, weak signals, and tests.\n6: \n7: ## LOC Counter\n8: \n9: | side | tool/status | version | notes |\n10: | --- | --- | --- | --- |\n11: | source | tokei | tokei 14.0.0 compiled with serialization support: json | Collected per-file LOC metrics with tokei. |\n12: | target | tokei | tokei 14.0.0 compiled with serialization support: json | Collected per-file LOC metrics with tokei. |\n13: \n14: ## Scale Ratios\n15: \n16: | ratio | target/source |\n17: | --- | --- |\n18: | targetToSourceFiles | 58.9% |\n19: | targetToSourceTextFiles | 59.4% |\n20: | targetToSourceNonblankLines | 89.6% |\n21: | targetToSourceProductionTextFiles | 51.9% |\n22: | targetToSourceProductionNonblankLines | 82.2% |\n23: | targetToSourceCodeFiles | 55.3% |\n24: | targetToSourceCodeNonblankLines | 54.2% |\n25: | targetToSourceProductionCodeFiles | 48.2% |\n26: | targetToSourceProductionCodeNonblankLines | 46.7% |\n27: | targetToSourceProductionCodeLines | 67.4% |\n28: | targetToSourceTestFiles | 450.0% |\n29: \n30: ## Findings\n31: \n32: | severity | kind | message |\n33: | --- | --- | --- |\n34: | medium | medium-loc-gap | Target production code LoC is below 75% of source production code LoC; verify that feature coverage is intentional and not hidden by tests or notes. |\n35: | medium | target-weakening-signals | Target code contains implementation-placeholder/stub/in-memory/deferred wording; verify each occurrence is intentional and documented. |\n36: | medium | target-structure-endpoint-concentration | 1 target file(s) carry a concentrated share of matrix targetEndpoints. Check whether unrelated source clusters are being closed through a broad shell instead of precise domain functions. |\n37: | medium | target-structure-broad-shell-endpoints | 2 broad shell-like target file(s) carry many coverage endpoints. Prefer targetEndpoints that name specific business functions or extracted modules. |\n38: | medium | target-structure-ui-surface-concentration | 2 target UI surface file(s) contain many page/view/dialog/list symbols. Split obvious settings/viewer/folder/about/player/gallery surfaces when they are becoming one long root shell. |\n39: | medium | target-structure-ui-endpoint-concentration | 12 target file(s) concentrate UI-related matrix endpoints. Check that routes are mutually rendered, back behavior is explicit, and UI evidence points at screen/page-specific builders rather than one debug-style shell. |\n40: \n41: ## Source Coverage Matrix\n42: \n43: | metric | value |\n44: | --- | --- |\n45: | expectedEntries | 260 |\n46: | expectedCriticalHighEntries | 224 |\n47: | actualEntries | 260 |\n48: | staleEntries | 0 |\n49: | missingCriticalHighEntries | 0 |\n50: | uncoveredCriticalHighEntries | 0 |\n51: | deferredCriticalHighEntries | 0 |\n52: | deferredCriticalHighRatio | 0.0 |\n53: | simplifiedCriticalHighEntries | 0 |\n54: | simplifiedCriticalHighRatio | 0.0 |\n55: | simplifiedWithoutReasonCriticalHighEntries | 0 |\n56: | simplifiedWithoutEndpointOrTestCriticalHighEntries | 0 |\n57: | incompleteDeferredCriticalHighEntries | 0 |\n58: | weakDeferredJustificationCriticalHighEntries | 0 |\n59: | genericDeferredTextCriticalHighEntries | 0 |\n60: | repeatedDeferredJustificationGroups | 0 |\n61: | repeatedImplementedEvidenceGroups | 0 |\n62: | repeatedImplementedEndpointGroups | 0 |\n63: | broadImplementedEndpointCriticalHighEntries | 0 |\n64: | unverifiedTestEvidenceCriticalHighEntries | 0 |\n65: | testEvidenceVerifiedByLatestTestGateEntries | 89 |\n66: | weakEvidenceCriticalHighEntries | 0 |\n67: | implementedWithoutEndpointOrTestCriticalHighEntries | 0 |\n68: | missingSourceBehaviorCriticalHighEntries | 0 |\n69: | missingTargetBehaviorCriticalHighEntries | 0 |\n70: | missingVerificationEvidenceCriticalHighEntries | 0 |\n71: | parityMismatchCriticalHighEntries | 0 |\n72: | allowedParityLevels | ['', 'deferred', 'equivalent', 'not-applicable', 'platform-replaced', 'simplified', 'unverified'] |\n73: | deferredRequiredFields | ['sourceEvidence', 'deferredReason', 'targetFallback', 'risk', 'futureCompletionPath'] |\n74: \n75: ### Matrix Status Counts\n76: \n77: | status | count |\n78: | --- | --- |\n79: | implemented | 114 |\n80: | not-applicable | 114 |\n81: | planned | 2 |\n82: | platform-replaced | 30 |\n83: \n84: ## Platform Capability Check\n85: \n86: | metric | value |\n87: | --- | --- |\n88: | expectedEntries | 6 |\n89: | expectedCriticalHighEntries | 6 |\n90: | actualEntries | 6 |\n91: | missingCriticalHighEntries | 0 |\n92: | unresolvedCriticalHighEntries | 0 |\n93: | missingDocSearchCriticalHighEntries | 0 |\n94: | implementedWeakTargetDecisionEntries | 0 |\n95: | implementedWeakTestEntries | 0 |\n96: | fallbackDespiteDirectEvidenceEntries | 0 |\n97: | localSimulationFallbackWithoutBlockerEntries | 0 |\n98: | replacementWithoutApiEvidenceEntries | 0 |\n99: | verifiedDirectMissingEndpointEntries | 0 |\n100: | implementedMissingEndpointEntries | 0 |\n101: | realCapabilityWithLocalFallbackEntries | 0 |\n102: | incompleteDeferredCriticalHighEntries | 0 |\n103: | genericDeferredCriticalHighEntries | 0 |\n104: | allowedStatuses | ['deferred', 'implemented-fallback', 'not-applicable', 'not-covered', 'planned', 'platform-replaced', 'unreviewed', 'verified-direct'] |\n105: | deferredRequiredFields | ['targetCapabilitySearch', 'blocker', 'targetFallback', 'futureCompletionPath'] |\n106: \n107: ### Platform Capability Status Counts\n108: \n109: | status | count |\n110: | --- | --- |\n111: | not-applicable | 4 |\n112: | platform-replaced | 1 |\n113: | verified-direct | 1 |\n114: \n115: ## Target Structure\n116: \n117: | metric | value |\n118: | --- | --- |\n119: | productionCodeFiles | 40 |\n120: | productionCodeNonblankLines | 3193 |\n121: | largestProductionCodeFileNonblankLines | 399 |\n122: | largeProductionCodeFiles | 0 |\n123: | endpointBearingFeatureRows | 144 |\n124: | endpointTargetFiles | 47 |\n125: | largestEndpointFileShare | 41.7% |\n126: | concentratedEndpointFiles | 1 |\n127: | broadShellEndpointFiles | 2 |\n128: | uiSurfaceFiles | 23 |\n129: | concentratedUiSurfaceFiles | 2 |\n130: | uiEndpointBearingFeatureRows | 135 |\n131: | uiEndpointTargetFiles | 46 |\n132: | concentratedUiEndpointFiles | 12 |\n133: | entryModuleStatus | PASS |\n134: | entryRootPackage | ohos_app_cangjie_entry |\n135: \n136: ## Target Weakening Signals\n137: \n138: | signal | count |\n139: | --- | --- |\n140: | todo | 1 |\n141: \n142: ## Must-Review Source Files\n143: \n144: | path | importance | LoC | category | risk tags |\n145: | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |\n146: | app/src/main/java/com/example/foodike/data/data_source/FakeData.kt | critical | 719 | kotlin-source | file_ops, image_viewer, intent_uri, navigation_resource, permissions |\n147: | app/src/main/java/com/example/foodike/presentation/details/RestaurantDetail.kt | critical | 296 | kotlin-source | image_viewer, intent_uri, navigation_resource, permissions, state_model |\n148: | app/src/main/java/com/example/foodike/presentation/history/components/HistorySection.kt | critical | 261 | kotlin-source | image_viewer, permissions |\n149: | app/src/main/jav