{"type":"text","timestamp":1782666989192,"sessionID":"ses_0f0cebc45ffeXm04RK0z9p3ABS","part":{"id":"prt_f0f3b57e2001zA0dzYUgcjvrOY","messageID":"msg_f0f3b2b60001cyuANvmmgy0l3k","sessionID":"ses_0f0cebc45ffeXm04RK0z9p3ABS","type":"text","text":"Changed files:\n- `Foodike-Harmony/entry/src/main/cangjie/ohos_app_cangjie_entry/features/profile/profile_store.cj`: added typed `ProfileAction` and `ProfileSection` enums plus explicit `actionFeedbackMessage(...)` and `sectionFeedbackMessage(...)` endpoints so the source’s intentional placeholder profile actions are represented as focused domain behavior instead of a shell-level stub.\n- `Foodike-Harmony/entry/src/main/cangjie/ohos_app_cangjie_entry/features/profile/profile_route_service.cj`: replaced the generic placeholder endpoint with explicit `editActionMessage()` and `sectionActionMessage(...)` service functions.\n- `Foodike-Harmony/entry/src/main/cangjie/ohos_app_cangjie_entry/features/profile/profile_page.cj`: made profile sections typed and passed section identity through `buildProfileSection(...)` and `renderProfileRoute(...)`.\n- `Foodike-Harmony/entry/src/main/cangjie/ohos_app_cangjie_entry/app/bootstrap_page.cj`: switched profile edit/section callbacks to the new focused profile endpoints.\n- `Foodike-Harmony/entry/src/test/cangjie/phase06_profile_capabilities_verification_test.cj`: added focused verification for the explicit edit/section action message endpoints and updated placeholder-action assertions to the new typed API.\n- `translation-inputs/source-coverage-matrix.json`: updated 5 authority rows to point at the repaired profile-specific endpoints and final-coverage test evidence.\n- `translation-inputs/source-coverage-matrix.md`: synced by the authority patch tool.\n- `translation-inputs/matrix-profile-final-repair-patch.json`: narrow authority patch payload used for the matrix update.\n\nCommands run:\n- `C:\\Users\\Sieger\\AppData\\Local\\Programs\\Python\\Python312\\python.exe -c \"...extract selected matrix row fields...\"`\n- `C:\\Users\\Sieger\\.cangjie-sdk\\6.1\\cangjie\\build-tools\\tools\\bin\\cjpm.exe test --target aarch64-linux-ohos` with the final-coverage env overlay from `translation-inputs/test-build-reports/final-coverage/test-build-report.md`\n- `C:\\Users\\Sieger\\AppData\\Local\\Programs\\Python\\Python312\\python.exe D:\\X2Cangjie\\X2Cangjie\\scripts\\shared\\source_coverage\\patch_authority.py --kind matrix --authority D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\translation-inputs\\source-coverage-matrix.json --patch D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\translation-inputs\\matrix-profile-final-repair-patch.json --markdown D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\translation-inputs\\source-coverage-matrix.md --plan-json D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\plan.json --target-project D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\Foodike-Harmony`\n\nBuild result:\n- PASS: focused target test reproduction succeeded with `cjpm test --target aarch64-linux-ohos` using the final-coverage recipe.\n- Reference report: `translation-inputs/test-build-reports/final-coverage/test-build-report.md`\n\nPlan changes:\n- none\n\nDeferred issues:\n- none added for this cluster\n- The `medium-loc-gap` child finding remains a whole-project warning signal, not a concrete missing profile behavior in this cluster. The current repair tightened real profile structure/evidence rather than inventing new behavior.\n- The broader whole-project structure warnings around `bootstrap_page.cj` endpoint concentration are still cross-cluster debt and were not fully addressed here because this prompt scoped the `implement-or-structure` report-finding cluster first.\n\nWhat I fixed:\n- Repaired the profile placeholder/action surface so it is explicitly source-backed and no longer looks like an unstructured shell stub.\n- Reduced shell-dependent evidence for profile rows by moving action semantics behind named profile endpoints.\n- Strengthened final evidence for the migrated source test placeholders by tying them to focused profile route/action tests and the accepted final-coverage harness pass.\n- Confirmed the `target-weakening-signals` report finding was not coming from live production profile code; the reported `todo` appears to come from generated artifacts, not target implementation logic.\n\nRemaining gaps:\n- No new functional blocker remains in this cluster.\n- Another final coverage pass is not required for this cluster specifically.\n- A separate pass is still reasonable for the remaining whole-project structure clusters if the goal is to reduce `bootstrap_page.cj` concentration warnings further.\n\nNext recommended action:\n- Sweep the next whole-project structure cluster and continue extracting precise non-shell endpoints from `bootstrap_page.cj`, starting with the largest remaining endpoint concentration rows.","time":{"start":1782666975202,"end":1782666989188}}}
